    <note>Chen(1) Ji [25] Ji(1)'s father is Zongdan [3089], son of Chengmin [3052]. Son Qi [3051] married Pang Ji's [1391] daughter. She was the mother of Chen(1) Shidao [3081]. Qi's son-in-law was Zhang(1) Shunmin [291]. Chen Shidao, in his funerary inscription for Ji's #2 son, C [14300], explicitly refers to a gene pool or hereditary transmission of talent: "Dafu you shi cai, go qi zi jie chang yu li" ([My] grandfather had hereditary [administrative talent], therefore all of his sons were strong in official (li) [abilities]). Chen Shidao, WJ, 16.8a, 9b; XCB, 160.1a, 165.13b, 178.14a; SHY:ZG, 65.1a. CBD, 3, 2450-51.</note>
